dataIdInfo.idAbs: This hospital point layer provides location information for mapping hospital facilities licensed by California Department of Public Health, Licensing and Certification. The dataset is a subset of the OSHPD Healthcare Facility dataset to include only facilities with a License_Type_Desc of 'hospital' and with a status of 'open' located in San Diego County and environs. The data snapshot was taken from OSHPD's ALIRTS system as of 30 June, 2018. Facility address information is maintained and provided by the Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development (OSHPD). The accuracy of the latitude/longitude geocodes are adequate for administrative planning purposes only. The data, on a case-by-case basis, may not be appropriate for driving directions, routing, emergency services, or other critical uses of the data.SanGIS downloaded the dataset from https://data.chhs.ca.gov/dataset/licensed-healthcare-facility-listingin csv format. Records within the County of San Diego and adjacent counties were selected and mapped using the latitude and longitude coordinates included with the dataset. The dataset was then projected to NAD_1983_StatePlane_California_VI_FIPS_0406_Feet. Only facilities with a license type description of 'hospital' that have a status of 'open' and that are located within a 25 mile radius of the County of San Diego were selected, with the exception of Imperial County, where vicinities within a 40 mile radius of The County of San Diego were included (as all facilities were beyond the 25 mile radius).

dataLineage.statement: This is a snapshot of the ALIRTS LHF_ETL_GEOSPATIAL (20121026) facility table that was created into a feature class. The snapshot of licensed healthcare facilities in California sometimes isn’t filled in entirely (lacking latitude and longitude for new facilities). The data was cleaned and purified for our process, removing duplicates, spaces before attribute entries (such as name, city, and zip). Previously researched data such as alias names or latitude and longitude is inserted into the file. For facilities with missing latitude and longitude, the WGS84DD geocoder is used to geocode the addresses given. If the geocoder can’t find an address, the address will be located and selected from the map by hand, known as pickpointing. New facilities also need alias names, these are based on their facility name, but truncated and scrutinized to remove unneeded parts (Inc., corporation, etc.). Geographic attributes based on spatial location are added to the facilities (county, census tract, mssa, etc.) using the Geographic Attribute tool. Finally the LHF Event Reprojection to NAD83 model is run to create the current feature class. Metadata is updated as a follow-up procedure.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: OSHPD Number A unique number established by the Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development (OSHPD) for identifying facilities and used in the Licensed Facility Information System (LFIS). The first three numbers identify the type of facility, the next two represent the county number, and the last five are randomly assigned within each county.
Facility License Level This identifies the level of the facility. Consolidated Facility Distinct Part Facility Parent Facility
County numbers are assigned to each California county from 1 - 58 in alphabetical order.
County name where facility is located

ER Service Level Hospital services providing immediate initial evaluation and treatment of acutely ill or injured patients on a 24-hour basis. See attached Data Dictionary for additional information. Licensed EMS levels are: 1. Standby: Provision of emergency medical care in a specifically designated area of the hospital that is equipped and maintained at all times to receive patients with urgent medical problems, and is capable of providing physician service within a reasonable time. 2. Basic: Provision of emergency medical care in a specifically designated area of the hospital that is staffed and equipped at all times to provide prompt care for any patient presenting urgent medical problems. 3. Comprehensive: Provision of diagnostic and therapeutic services for unforeseen physical and mental disorders that, if not properly treated, would lead to marked suffering, disability, or death. The scope of services is comprehensive with in-house capability for managing all medical situations on a definitive and continuing basis. 4. Trauma: Emergency rooms which are staffed and equipped at the highest level to treat any and all severe trauma cases. A local Emergency Medical Services Agency determines the level of designation. 5. Blank or Not Applicable means that the hospital or healthcare facility does not have emergency services
License status of facility as of report date. Only facilities with a status of 'open' were included in this dataset
Effective date of the facility status
Type of facility that is licensed: Clinic Home Health Agency/Hospital Hospice Facility Hospital Long Term Care Facility
Specific category of license type: Acute Psychiatric Hospital Chemical dep. Recovery Hospital General Acute Care Hospital Psychiatric Health Facility
License Number License number of the facility as assigned by the California Department of Public Health.

overview.eaover:
A list of California healthcare facilities licensed by California Department of Public Health, Licensing and Certification. To link the OSHPD IDs with those from other Departments, like CDPH, please reference the "Licensed Facility Cross-Walk" Open Data table at https://data.chhs.ca.gov/dataset/licensed-facility-crosswalk
Key fields in the dataset are LICENSE_TYPE_DESC so that major types of facilities can be filtered (Clinic, Hospice, Hospital, Long Term Care Facility). The LICENSE_CATEGORY_DESC field is particularly important for further definition of a facility, such as type of hospital (e.g. General Acute Care Hospital, Psychiatric Health Facility, Chemical Dep. Recovery Hospital or Acute Psychiatric Hospital). The ER_SERVICE_LEVEL_DESC field is also a key field for hospitals (Emergency-Basic, Emergency - Comprehensive, None, Not Applicable).
See individual field definitions for further details.
